==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Secession
<hw>Se*ces"sion</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*s⟦ecr⟧sh"⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>secessio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>s⟦eacute⟧cession</ets>. See
<er>Secede</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of seceding; separation
from fellowship or association with others, as in a religious or
political organization; withdrawal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(U.S. Hist.)</fld> <def>The withdrawal of a State
from the national Union.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Secession Church</b></col><cd> (in Scotland). See
<er>Seceder</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secessionism</ent>⟦br⟧
